What are ANGOSTURA® bitters? How do you use them? Where did they come from? And what's up with that iconic oversized bottle label? 

We answer all these questions and more in this Bitters 101 lesson with Greg Titian of @How2Drink. Watch him dash his way through the history, purpose and power of ANGOSTURA® bitters – a bartender's salt and pepper.

node.text:
It's tough to accept but Summer doesn't last forever, so we encourage you to make the most of the remaining days. Take advantage of the fleeting season with a cocktail that emanates Summer vibes. The Cottage Rum Punch is a tropical, fruit-forward, refresher that is best served in the sun. 

Recipe and image c/o: @cheerstohappyhour 

2 oz Rum 
0.5 oz Coconut Syrup 
1 oz Orange Juice 
1 oz Lime Juice 
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters 
Short shake all ingredients with ice and strain into a rocks glass filled with pebble ice. 
Top with ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters until satisfied. 
Garnish with mint

node.text:
National Rum Day calls for a little history. For those of you new to the ANGOSTURA's Queen’s Park Swizzle™ — this creation came to be in 1893 as the house cocktail of the Queen's Park Hotel in Port of Spain, Trinidad. 

A few tips + tricks so you can make this cocktail with us:
1. The swizzle stick allows you to mix right in the glass but if you don't have one, you can also use a bar spoon.
2. The punch of clove in ANGOSTURA® Aromatic Bitters gives this beverage its iconic taste.
3. Finish off with crushed ice on top and don't be afraid to add a few extra dashes for a snow cone effect.

node.text:
Some believe that mint brings good luck. And today, you might need it.

We can't make any promises, but then again, how unlucky can you be with a mojito in-hand? #FridayThe13th

Apple and Ginger Mojito
1 ¾ oz Angostura® 5-Year Gold Rum
10 mint leaves
½ oz fresh lime juice
½ oz simple syrup
¾ oz apple juice
3 dashes Angostura® aromatic bitters
Ginger beer
Garnish: Mint Sprig & Apple Fan
Glass: Highball

METHOD
Place all ingredients (except for the ginger beer and apple juice) in a highball glass. Muddle mint gently to extract flavour. Add the apple juice and some crushed ice. Gently stir the drink and top up with ginger beer and Angostura® aromatic bitters.

This one is for the tequila lovers who are tired of margaritas. Spice up your Happy Hour routine with this refreshing twist on a Calvados Pucker. Using ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters to add spice and Green Chartreuse for an herbal flair, this tequila cocktail is a complex palate pleaser that's ideal for summertime sipping in between great conversations. Swipe for the recipe specs.

CC: @idealistfoods 

Silver Apple Recipe:
1 1/2 oz Tequila Plata/Silver/Blanco
1/2 oz Calvados
1 oz fresh lemon juice
1/2 oz simple syrup
1 bar spoon Green Chartreuse
1 bar spoon Velvet Falernum
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters

Method: Add all ingredients to a shaking tin with ice. Shake until chilled and diluted, about 10 - 15 seconds. Strain into a chilled coupe. Garnish with a twist of lemon. Sip, savor, and drink the sunshine in.

If you’re looking for ways to use your ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters, here’s a twofer. Both classics in their own regard, The Espresso Martini and The Widow’s Kiss – fortunately, classics never go out of style. They’re each as elegant as they are refreshing.

Espresso Martini:
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters
1 ½ oz Vodka
1 oz Espresso Coffee
2/3 oz coffee liqueur
1 pinch salt (optional)

Garnish: Lemon zest twist (discarded) plus float three coffee beans on the surface

Method: Shake all ingredients with ice and fine strain into chilled glass

Widow's Kiss Recipe:
3 dashes ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters
1 ½ oz Cognac
½ oz Benedictine
½ oz Green Chartreuse

Method: Add ingredients to mixing glass. Add ice, and stir for 12 seconds. Strain into chilled Nick and Nora glass.
#ANGOSTURA #ANGOSTURAbitters #Mixology #Cocktails #Recipe #Cheers #HappyHour

National Daiquiri Day is best spent celebrating with ANGOSTURA® 1919. We're adding some summer flavor with notes of passionfruit. Tell us your favorite way to mix in a seasonal spin to this classic cocktail.

Passionfruit Daiquiri:
2 oz Angostura 1919 Rum
¾ oz fresh lime juice
¾ oz passionfruit syrup
3 dashes Angostura orange bitters
Add the rum, bitters, lime, syrup and ice.  Shake until well-chilled. Double-strain into a coupe glass. Garnish with a lime wheel.

If you've mastered the Old Fashioned, it's time to challenge yourself. Get creative at the bar cart by trying new twists on the beloved classic. You can swap spirits, experiment with new garnishes and even add flavors. Check out @allequalparts' Pecan Pie Old Fashioned below for inspiration.

Pecan Pie Old Fashioned:
2 oz Standard Proof Pecan Whiskey
1 tsp Maple Syrup
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® cocoa bitters
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters

Method: Add everything to a mixing glass with ice. Stir and strain over fresh ice. Garnish with a lemon twist.

#ANGOSTURA #ANGOSTURAbitters #Mixology #Bartending #Cocktails

The only thing you should be straining this weekend is a your favorite cocktail made with ANGOSTURA® bitters. Swipe for a look at this twist on the signature Manhattan.

Image and recipe c/o: @flavoursum 

Recipe: 
1 3/4 oz Rye
3/4 oz Sweet Vermouth
2 dashes ANGOSTURA® aromatic bitters
1 dash ANGOSTURA® orange bitters
3 maraschino cherries

Method: 
1. Stir all ingredients in a cocktail jug with ice for 3 minutes
2. Strain and pour into a glass
3. Add a cherry
